<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5760] Missing argument in some XJ022 errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5760</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EmbedBlob and EmbedClob some times wrap IOExceptions in an SQLException with SQLState XJ022 (SQLState.SET_STREAM_FAILURE), but they don&apos;t always specify the message argument, so the error message ends up like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.sql.SQLException: Unable to set stream: &apos;&lt;/p&gt;
{0}
&lt;p&gt;&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(The detailed error message does appear in a chained exception, so it&apos;s not a very big problem, but it looks a bit odd.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know of a way to expose these exceptions in a test. I just noticed it when I added some manual asserts to force a failure when investigating another issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix should be simple: Use the helper method Util.setStreamFailure() that sets the message argument automatically.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
